<p><a name="Popular_culture" id="Popular_culture"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Hmong_people&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14" title="Edit section: Popular culture">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Popular culture</span></h2>
<p>Hmong culture in Highland Park, Michigan, is explored in the film <i><a href="/wiki/Gran_Torino_(film)" title="Gran Torino (film)">Gran Torino</a></i>, released on January 9, 2009 and directed by <a href="/wiki/Clint_Eastwood" title="Clint Eastwood">Clint Eastwood</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-55" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-55" title=""><span>[</span>56<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>Also, a patient in the television series <i><a href="/wiki/Grey%27s_Anatomy" title="Grey's Anatomy">Grey's Anatomy</a></i>, <a href="/wiki/Grey%27s_Anatomy_(season_2)" title="Grey's Anatomy (season 2)" class="mw-redirect">season 2</a>, episode 5 was of Hmong origin. <a href="/wiki/Brenda_Song" title="Brenda Song">Brenda Song</a>, of <i><a href="/wiki/The_Suite_Life_of_Zack_%26_Cody" title="The Suite Life of Zack &amp; Cody">The Suite Life of Zack &amp; Cody</a></i>, is of Hmong and Thai origin.</p>
